cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with generating adversarial examples for neural network-based image classifiers, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses limited query access and partial-information settings, which are relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of natural evolution strategies and targeted attacks suggests a connection to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
